RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GALACTIC CORE ran in the middle of the pack on the outside then coming down the stretch got bumped by foe when they swerved to miss a fallen foe. GOLDEN GREEK ran on the outside in the middle of the pack followed behind GALACTIC CORE then coming down the stretch started to duel GALACTIC CORE when they had to swerve to miss a fallen foe, just missed the win by a head. BARON'S SONG ran off pace from the leaders then coming down the stretch barely had enough time to dodge a fallen foe in their path. STACKERS ran at the back of the pack then coming out of the turn took a wide outside bid to make up distance to pass most of the pack dodging a fallen foe. STORMIN ATTILA ran in the middle of the pack then coming down the stretch on the outside of GALACTIC CORE when they had to dodge a fallen foe they pushed him out further outside. PARS AND BIRDIES was never far back then in the middle of the turn steadied pace and maintained an even thru the finish line. OLD FASHION TIME ran at the back of the pack on the rail then drifted out slightly on the stretch just to dodged a fallen foe back to the rail to finish out the race. MIST N SEVEN ran at the back of the pack then late stretch after passing an accident by a foe, they passed the tired foes. MEMOLOTSAMISCHIEF had good early speed led for a little over half of the race then faded hard coming on to the stretch taking a very wide outside path. CHAOTIC KENT ran with an even pace in the middle of the pack then faded late into the stretch. SLOWDOWNTOGOFAST ran at the back of the pack then eased after the turn to gallop across the wire. BYE BYE RAY vanned off, did not finish. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIRT FLIRT ran at the back of the pack then coming on the stretch in the seven path had a tremendous drive to over take six foes to win. BORN TO REIGN ran on the outside in the middle of the pack then coming down the stretch seeing a foe pass on the outside decided to follow them for place. TIZ FOR REAL ran at the back of the pack then dueled with BORN TO REIGN for a short while down the stretch. SHE HIT A HOMER bumped by foe at break, then ran with an even pace in the middle of the pack then had a late bid on the inside to overtake foes. TIZ MY HOUR bumped foe at break, then ran with a steady pace in the middle of the pack then slowly shuffled back as they came on to the stretch. WAY RITE ran with an even pace throughout the race. CAROLYN'S WAY ran at the front of the main pack then faded back late into the stretch. OLIVIAN had tremendous speed leaving the gate, then mid way down the stretch faded hard dropping back to eighth.
